headline: Alexandria Real Estate Equities: Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The Pasadena, California-based real estate investment trust said it had funds from operations of $377.8 million, or $2.22 per share, in the period. The average estimate of four analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of $2.31 per share. Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry.
